# End-To-End Offline First Implementation Plan (Supabase Supported)

## Problem Statement
Currently, both the Admin Dashboard and the Expo App use hardcoded demo arrays (`INITIAL_STALLS`, `DEMO_FEED`, etc.) in memory. The app does not load from the local SQLite db, and [syncRemoteDown](file:///c:/WebDev/websiteBuilder/KaggleGithubV1/expo-template/src/services/storage.ts#116-141) only simulates fetching. Config patching is allowed dynamically at runtime, violating the Build Freeze Rule.

## Proposed Changes

### 1. Manual Supabase Setup (Prerequisite)
You will need to run the following SQL script in your Supabase SQL Editor to create the necessary tables for the app features:

```sql
-- STALLS TABLE
create table public.stalls (
  id uuid default gen_random_uuid() primary key,
  app_id text not null, -- Links the stall to a specific AI generated app
  name text not null,
  category text not null,
  price_range text,
  is_featured boolean default false,
  emoji text,
  created_at timestamp with time zone default timezone('utc'::text, now()) not null
);

-- ANNOUNCEMENTS TABLE
create table public.announcements (
  id uuid default gen_random_uuid() primary key,
  app_id text not null,
  type text not null, -- 'alert', 'event', 'result', 'update'
  title text not null,
  body text not null,
  is_pinned boolean default false,
  created_at timestamp with time zone default timezone('utc'::text, now()) not null
);

-- Optionally disable RLS for hackathon speed (or configure policies properly)
alter table public.stalls disable row level security;
alter table public.announcements disable row level security;
```

### 2. Admin Dashboard Integration (Next.js)
#### [MODIFY] [frontend/src/app/dashboard/event-admin/[appId]/stalls/page.tsx](file:///c:/WebDev/websiteBuilder/KaggleGithubV1/frontend/src/app/dashboard/event-admin/%5BappId%5D/stalls/page.tsx)
